<bug>
	<id>22643</id>
	<title>Docker and runc get out of sync1.12.0</title>
	<description>
		<paragraph id="1">
			<sentence id="1.1">Given this test program (test.sh):
```
set -ex
docker run -d --name test -ti ubuntu top
while true ; do
 docker pause test
 docker unpause test
done
```</sentence>
		</paragraph>
		<paragraph id="2">
			<sentence id="2.1">If I let it run for a while, around 30 minutes or so, I eventually see this:
```
...
++ docker pause test
test
++ docker unpause test
test
++ true
++ docker pause test
test
++ docker unpause test
Failed to unpause container (test): Error response from daemon: Cannot 
unpause container aca8355a0051211267b5784b5e4cf32ef04c1681dd0d867234a8f5b7c921681d: 
rpc error: code = 2 desc = ""
```</sentence>
		</paragraph>
		<paragraph id="3">
			<sentence id="3.1">Then trying to unpause that container manually, I then see:
```
$ docker unpause test
Failed to unpause container (test): Error response from daemon: Cannot 
unpause container aca8355a0051211267b5784b5e4cf32ef04c1681dd0d867234a8f5b7c921681d: 
rpc error: code = 2 desc = "container not paused
"
```</sentence>
		</paragraph>
		<paragraph id="4">
			<sentence id="4.1">Notice the "desc" field has something this time.</sentence>
		</paragraph>
		<paragraph id="5">
			<sentence id="5.1">When I go into `runc` and manually pause the container and restart my script it all works ok.</sentence>
			<sentence id="5.2">So it looks like the issue is just that `runc` and the engine got out of sync somehow, everything seems to still be in an ok state.</sentence>
		</paragraph>
		<paragraph id="6">
			<sentence id="6.1">I wanted to dig a little deeper before I posted the issue but I keep getting distracted so I decided to go ahead in case someone else has the time to track this down before I get a chance to.</sentence>
		</paragraph>
		<paragraph id="7">
			<sentence id="7.1">I'm using master (post 1.11) that's only a few days old.</sentence>
		</paragraph>
		<paragraph id="8">
			<sentence id="8.1">ping @crosbymichael @LK4D4</sentence>
		</paragraph>
	</description>
